Package ohos.security.asset

Class AssetOperatorAbs

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.security.asset.AssetOperatorAbs

  • public abstract class AssetOperatorAbs
extends Object
    An abstract class that provides the abstract methods for storing key asset data.

    The abstract methods can be used to securely store, delete, update, and query key asset data, such as usernames and passwords.

    Before calling the methods of this class, you must call the AssetOperator.getInstance() method to obtain an AssetOperatorAbs instance.

    Since:
    1
    SystemCapability
    SystemCapability.security.asset

      • assetInsert

        public abstract AssetResult assetInsert​(Ability ability,
                                        IntentParams intentParams)
        Encrypts and stores a piece of asset data in the system database.
        Parameters:
        ability - Indicates the Ability object used to obtain the application context.
        intentParams - Indicates the IntentParams object, which consists of a key-value pair. To define a method for performing a specific operation, invoke IntentParams.setParam to set the key and value. The key parameters include AssetOperator#INTENT_PARAMS_KEY_APPTAG, AssetOperator#INTENT_PARAMS_KEY_BATCHASSET, AssetOperator#INTENT_PARAMS_KEY_AEADASSET, AssetOperator#INTENT_PARAMS_KEY_EXTINFO, and AssetOperator#INTENT_PARAMS_KEY_ASSETTYPE.
        Returns:
        Returns the AssetResult instance, including AssetResult.resultCode and AssetResult.resultInfo.
          AssetResult.resultCode can be any of the following:
        • AssetOperator#SUCCESS
        • AssetOperator#ERROR_CODE_INVALID_ARGUMENT
        • AssetOperator#ERROR_CODE_PERMISSION_DENIED
        • AssetOperator#ERROR_CODE_UNINITIALIZED
        • AssetOperator#ERROR_CODE_DATABASE_ERROR
        • AssetOperator#ERROR_CODE_UNSECURED_ENVIRONMENT
        • AssetOperator#ERROR_CODE_SYSTEM_ERROR
          AssetResult.resultInfo can be either of the following:
        • Operation succeeds: asset data index value obtained using the resultInfo.get(0) method
        • Operation fails: null
        Since:
        1
